{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idcf646f8a-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0","identifier":"/us/usc/t48/s864"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"864"},"text":"§ 864.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Appeals, certiorari, removal of causes, etc.; use of English language","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The laws of the United States relating to appeals, certiorari, removal of causes, and other matters or proceedings as between the courts of the United States and the courts of the several States shall govern in such matters and proceedings as between the United States District Court for the District of Puerto Rico and the courts of Puerto Rico.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"All pleadings and proceedings in the United States District Court for the District of Puerto Rico shall be conducted in the English language.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idcf646f8b-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1900-04-12/ch191/s35"},"text":"Apr. 12, 1900, ch. 191, § 35","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/31/85"},"text":"31 Stat. 85","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1917-03-02/ch145/s42"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1917, ch. 145, § 42","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/39/966"},"text":"39 Stat. 966","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1925-02-13/ch229/s13"},"text":"Feb. 13, 1925, ch. 229, § 13","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/43/942"},"text":"43 Stat. 942","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1928-01-31/ch14/s1"},"text":"Jan. 31, 1928, ch. 14, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/45/54"},"text":"45 Stat. 54","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1932-05-17/ch190"},"text":"May 17, 1932, ch. 190","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/47/158"},"text":"47 Stat. 158","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646/s21"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 646, § 21","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/990"},"text":"62 Stat. 990","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idcf646f8c-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcf646f8d-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idcf646f8e-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The laws of the United States relating to appeals, certiorari, removal of causes, and other matters or proceedings, referred to in text, are classified to Title 28, Judiciary and Judicial Procedure.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idcf646f8f-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“United States District Court for the District of Puerto Rico” substituted in text for “District Court of the United States for Puerto Rico” in view of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s132/a"},"text":"section 132(a) of Title 28","children":[],"tail":", Judiciary and Judicial Procedure, which states that “There shall be in each judicial district a district court which shall be a court of record known as the United States District Court for the district” and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s119"},"text":"section 119 of Title 28","children":[],"tail":", which states that “Puerto Rico constitutes one judicial district.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idcf646f90-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s244"},"text":"Act Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 244","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/1157"},"text":"36 Stat. 1157","children":[],"tail":", related to direct appeals from The Supreme Court and the United District Court for Puerto Rico to the United States Supreme Court, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1915-01-28/ch22/s3"},"text":"act Jan. 28, 1915, ch. 22, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/804"},"text":"38 Stat. 804","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1900-04-12/ch191/s34"},"text":"act Apr. 12, 1900, ch. 191, § 34","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/31/84"},"text":"31 Stat. 84","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcf646f91-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1948—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1948","children":[],"tail":", amended section generally, and struck out provisions relating to the term of district court and appeals to the circuit court."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1928—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1928-01-31"},"text":"Jan. 31, 1928","children":[],"tail":", abolished writ of error in civil and criminal cases and made all relief formerly obtained by writ of error obtainable by appeal."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1925—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1925-02-13/ch229/s13"},"text":"Act Feb. 13, 1925, ch. 229, § 13","children":[],"tail":", repealed provisions of this section permitting a direct review by the Supreme Court of cases in the courts in Puerto Rico."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idcf646f92-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"idcf646f93-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Puerto Rico” substituted in text for “Porto Rico” pursuant to act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1932-05-17"},"text":"May 17, 1932","children":[],"tail":", which is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t48/s731a"},"text":"section 731a of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idcf646f94-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1948 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1948","children":[],"tail":", effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-09-01"},"text":"Sept. 1, 1948","children":[],"tail":", see section 38 of that act, set out as an Effective Date note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s1"},"text":"section 1 of Title 28","children":[],"tail":", Judiciary and Judicial Procedure."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"repeals","id":"idcf646f95-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Repeals","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 39 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1948","children":[],"tail":", repealed section 1 of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1925-02-13/ch229"},"text":"act Feb. 13, 1925, ch. 229","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/43/936"},"text":"43 Stat. 936","children":[],"tail":", formerly cited as a credit to this section, which authorized review in the Circuit Court of Appeals in the First Circuit."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
